<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-03-27T21:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-03-27T21:00:00-05:00" n="377" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d377">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.51/7452b: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Gauss</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-03-27T22:00:00-04:00">March 27,
                                    1942—10 p.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>231. Reference second paragraph Department’s 216, March 25, 11 p.m.<note n="19a" xml:id="d377fn1">Not printed.</note> The Chinese Minister
                            for Foreign Affairs has requested that his letter of March 21 to the
                            Secretary of the Treasury be amended to include a phrase to the effect
                            that the channel through which the Chinese Government would keep the
                            Secretary of the Treasury informed would be the Chinese Minister of
                            Finance.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Welles</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>